-- Fiat-Chrysler CEO says talks with Russia on possible plant continue
-- 
-- Mon Mar 31, 2014 07:26AM EDT
-- None



TORINO, Italy, March 31 (Reuters) - Fiat Chrysler <FIA.MI> is continuing talks with Russia on a possible collaboration that could see the company setting up a new plant there to produce Jeeps and light commercial vehicles, its Chief Executive Sergio Marchionne said on Monday.

"Russia continues to be a market of strategic relevance," Marchionne told a shareholders' meeting.